<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>e) Construct a semantic link network of pictures, tags and language representations in relevant texts as the summary.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>The semantic link networks of texts, pictures, tags and users indicate a kind of social semantics of picture usage and thus provide the ground for selection.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>So, the techniques of text summary can be extended to the construction of semantic link network and image retrieval [Gudivada and Raghavan, 1995].</a>
